{
  "texts": [
    "Knowing that a highly accurate model likely made a mistake on a given example, along with its reasoning for it, can nudge the reviewer to consider why the model erred and preempt them from making the same mistake.",
    "Surprisingly, we find that these explanations point to the correct evidence (§5).",
    "In this section, we present criteria that can be used to determine the suitability of tasks for application-grounded human evaluations of explanations (§3.1) and analyze 53 existing datasets introduced for developing and evaluating explanations in NLP (§3.2).",
    "We refer to a task as its realization in the data.",
    "We determine that the following criteria must be fulfilled to ensure that evaluations are rooted in genuine human-AI interactions: c 1: The task has a meaningful connection to a real-world application, involving people who seek model outputs and act on them."
  ]
}